    <!-- About Section -->
    <section class="section" id="about">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title">What is Telecommunications Engineering?</h2>
            <div class="content-wrapper">
                <div class="text-content">
                    <p>Telecommunications Engineering is a specialized branch of electrical engineering that focuses on the design, development, and maintenance of systems that transmit information over distances. It encompasses the study of wired and wireless communication technologies that enable voice, data, and video transmission across local and global networks.</p>
                    <p>As a telecommunications engineer, you'll work on creating and improving the infrastructure that connects our world, from cellular networks and satellite systems to fiber optic cables and internet protocols. You'll apply principles of signal processing, network theory, and information theory to develop reliable and efficient communication systems.</p>
                    <p>This field is at the heart of our connected society, enabling technologies like mobile phones, broadband internet, IoT devices, and broadcasting systems. With the continuous evolution of communication technologies, telecommunications engineers are constantly innovating to meet the growing demand for faster, more reliable, and more secure communication networks.</p>
                </div>
                <div class="image-content">
                    <img src="https://images.unsplash.com/photo-1544197150-b99a580bb7a8?ixlib=rb-1.2.1&auto=format&fit=crop&w=1350&q=80" alt="Telecommunications Engineering">
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

    <!-- Key Areas Section -->
    <section class="section bg-dark" id="key-areas">
        <div class="container">
            <h2 class="section-title" style="color: var(--light-text);">Key Areas of Study</h2>
            <p class="section-intro" style="color: var(--light-text);">Telecommunications Engineering encompasses several specialized areas that form the foundation of modern communication systems:</p>
            
            <div class="cards-grid three-columns">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-broadcast-tower"></i> Wireless Communications</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of transmitting information over the air using electromagnetic waves. This includes cellular networks, satellite communications, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth, and other wireless technologies.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Radio Frequency Engineering</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Antenna design, propagation models, link budgets</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Cellular Networks</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">4G/5G technologies, network planning, optimization</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Wireless Protocols</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">IEEE 802.11, Bluetooth, ZigBee, LoRa</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-network-wired"></i> Network Engineering</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The design and implementation of communication networks that enable data exchange between devices. This includes local area networks (LANs), wide area networks (WANs), and the Internet.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Network Protocols</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">TCP/IP, routing protocols, QoS mechanisms</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Network Architecture</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">OSI model, network topologies, SDN</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Network Security</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Encryption, firewalls, intrusion detection</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-wave-square"></i> Signal Processing</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The manipulation of signals to improve transmission efficiency, reliability, and quality. This includes modulation techniques, error correction, and filtering to optimize communication systems.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Digital Signal Processing</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Filtering, sampling, FFT analysis</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Modulation Techniques</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">AM, FM, PSK, QAM, OFDM</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Error Correction</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">FEC, channel coding, interleaving</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

            <div class="cards-grid three-columns" style="margin-top: 1.5rem;">
                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-project-diagram"></i> Optical Communications</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The transmission of information using light waves through optical fibers. This includes fiber optic technology, optical network design, and photonic systems for high-speed data transmission.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Fiber Optic Technology</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Single-mode/multi-mode fibers, dispersion, attenuation</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Optical Network Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">SONET/SDH, WDM, PON architectures</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Photonic Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Optical transmitters, receivers, amplifiers</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-satellite"></i> Satellite Communications</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The use of artificial satellites to provide communication links across large distances. This includes satellite system design, orbital mechanics, and earth station engineering.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Satellite Systems</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">GEO, MEO, LEO constellations, transponders</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Earth Station Design</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Antenna systems, tracking, VSAT networks</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Satellite Access</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">FDMA, TDMA, CDMA, multiple access techniques</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>

                <div class="card">
                    <div class="card-header">
                        <h3><i class="fas fa-mobile-alt"></i> Mobile Communications</h3>
                    </div>
                    <div class="card-content">
                        <p>The study of communication systems that enable users to maintain connections while moving. This includes cellular networks, mobile devices, and mobility management protocols.</p>
                        <ul class="skills-list">
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Cellular Technology</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">GSM, UMTS, LTE, 5G architectures</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Mobility Management</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Handover, roaming, location tracking</p>
                            </li>
                            <li>
                                <span class="skill-name">Mobile Network Planning</span>
                                <p class="skill-desc">Coverage, capacity, interference management</p>
                            </li>
                        </ul>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
    </section>

